Mar 30 2007 	Fun for the Kids	We visited CoCo Keys in early March. With two children, ages 6 &amp; 7, the waterpark was a big hit. There is a zero depth area that has basketball nets and two small tot-friendly slides. There is a multi-level play area that leads to the bigger slides. Also a lazy river and a hot tub, in addition to a non-zero depth pool. Be sure to see CoCo the (real!!) red parrot at the towel pick-up. Lots of places to sit or recline and you can even rent private cabanas for an additional fee. Food service was okay...there is a Pizza Hut and A &amp; W for pizza, hot dogs, that sort of thing. Definintely a great way to spend the day!!	
